Type: Package
Package: gllvmTMB
Title: Stacked-Trait GLLVMs with TMB
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Shinichi", "Nakagawa", , "itchyshin@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7765-5182"))
Description: A standalone Template Model Builder (TMB) package for
    stacked-trait, long-format multivariate generalised linear latent
    variable models (GLLVMs). The 3 x 5 covariance keyword grid pairs
    correlation structure (none / phylogenetic / spatial) with covariance
    mode (scalar / unique / indep / dep / latent). A reduced-rank latent
    decomposition (Lambda Lambda^T + diag(psi)) is the canonical
    multivariate option; full unstructured and marginal modes are also
    supported. Phylogenetic models use a sparse A^-1 representation
    (Hadfield & Nakagawa 2010), the engine is built on Template Model
    Builder (Kristensen et al. 2016), and spatial models use the SPDE /
    GMRF approximation with R-side helpers inherited from 'sdmTMB'
    (Anderson et al. 2025). See Kristensen et al. (2016)
    <doi:10.18637/jss.v070.i05>, Anderson et al. (2025)
    <doi:10.18637/jss.v115.i02>, and Hadfield & Nakagawa (2010)
    <doi:10.1111/j.1420-9101.2009.01915.x>. Upstream copyright
    holders of inherited code are listed in 'inst/COPYRIGHTS'.
